{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/background-information/prevalence/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"c6ce3955-0c4a-5f77-9321-bcbe79422612","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 83bea6bc-305b-4cf8-93cc-4ad6b3f2989d --><h2>How common is it?</h2><!-- end field 83bea6bc-305b-4cf8-93cc-4ad6b3f2989d -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item afb6a07e-a323-4725-9b81-1bc6d0851be9 --><!-- begin field 1d381e21-0d23-47dd-953a-a9853b21e4dc --><ul><li><strong>The prevalence of pilonidal sinus disease has been estimated at</strong> 26 cases per 100,000 people in the United States [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Choy, 2019</a>], 25 cases per 100,000 people in a French study, and 28 cases per 100,000 people in a Norwegian report [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Harris, 2016</a>].</li><li>Pilonidal sinus disease is more common in men (2–4 times more likely than in women) and in people aged 15–40 years (the mean age at presentation has been reported as 21 years in males and 19 years in females) [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Kober, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Choy, 2019</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field 1d381e21-0d23-47dd-953a-a9853b21e4dc --><!-- end item afb6a07e-a323-4725-9b81-1bc6d0851be9 -->","topic":{"id":"c75a0f03-60df-5718-b4ad-d6e32f354f69","topicId":"f6f74445